<html>
  <%- include("./head", {title: "Books"}) %>

  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <%- include("./nav") %>
      <h1 class="text-center">The Most Noteworthy Books of All Time</h1>
      <div class="spacer"></div>

      <center>
        <img src="books.png" />
      </center>
      <br>

      <blockquote class="main-quote text-center">
        A man's mind may be likened to a garden, which may be intelligently cultivated or allowed to run wild; but whether cultivated or neglected, it must, and will, <em>bring forth.</em>
      </blockquote>
      <p class="text-center">- <em>As a Man Thinketh</em></p>
      <br>

      <p>To reduce the likelihood of anyoneâ€™s biases, objectives, or blind spots affecting this list too much, only books that appear in at least two of the following lists are included:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Encyclopedia Brittanica's <em><a href="https://www.britannica.com/list/12-novels-considered-the-greatest-book-ever-written">12 Novels Considered the "Greatest Book Ever Written"</a></em></li>
        <li>Open Education Database's <em><a href="https://oedb.org/ilibrarian/50_books_that_changed_the_world/">50 Most Influential Books of All Time</a></em></li>
        <li>Bokklubben World Library's <em><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bokklubben_World_Library">100 Best Books of All Time</a></em></li>
        <li>Wikipedia's <em><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_best-selling_books">Best-Selling Books</a></em></li>
        <li>Jordan Peterson's <em><a href="https://www.jordanbpeterson.com/great-books/">Great Books List</a></em></li>
        <li>Thomas Jefferson Education's <em><a href="https://tjed.org/resources/classics/">Classics</a></em></li>
        <li>Art of Manliness's <em><a href="https://www.artofmanliness.com/articles/100-books-every-man-read/">100 Books Every Man Should Read</a></em></li>
      </ol>
      <br>

      <% Object.keys(booksData).reverse().forEach(function(key){ %>
      <h2>
        <% if (key == 6) { %>Six
        <% } else if (key == 5) { %>Five
        <% } else if (key == 4) { %>Four
        <% } else if (key == 3) { %>Three
        <% } else if (key == 2) { %>Two
        <% } %> List Appearances
      </h2>
      <% booksData[key].forEach(function(ele){ %>
        <li class="book-list"><em><a href="/books/<%= ele.page_name %>"><%= ele.name %></a></em><% if (ele.author.length > 0) { %>, by <%= ele.author %><% } %></li>
      <% }) %> <br><% }) %>

      <%- include("./footer") %>

    </div>
  </body>
</html>
